[The update on ASF in Russia, published by a Belarusian news agency, reflects the grave concern in Belarus about the situation in neighbouring Russia, from where repeated introductions of the disease are feared. Belarus reported to the OIE in July 2013 about its 1st (Grodno oblast, bordering Lithuania) and 2nd (Vitebsk oblast, bordering Russia) ASF outbreaks. Since the publication of Belarus' follow-up report No 2, on 29 Jul 2013, no additional reports have been submitted.

We have been unofficially told that the policy undertaken in Belarus includes large-scale killings of wild boars. Confirmation or otherwise and figures will be helpful.

Since the start of the current (continuing) ASF epizootic in Russia, on 11 Sep 2009, Russia submitted 101 follow-up reports, the most recent one on 4 Sep 2013, pertaining to 261 outbreaks. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1rTw.]
